cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC

The paper discusses the performance of deep and wide convolutional neural networks on a neuromorphic system for object recognition tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.AI) for classification tasks. Additionally, the paper evaluates the efficiency of different architectures, which falls under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the potential impact of the results on human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
